\nmodels, though our rough estimates fall short of the requirements for extremely\nbright events if these are powered by radioactive decay. However, approximate\nlight curves of our models suggest that a proto-magnetar or black hole\nspin-down may fuel luminous transients (with peak luminosities ~ 10^{43...44}\nerg).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Aug 2021 14:17:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 Apr 2022 13:32:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-05"}
